name: window.lf (adhd edition)
description: A window for jjjjjjjjjjohn into code from the 60s, 70s, and 80s made with the LOGO programming language (1967) on an IBM XT using IBM LOGO.EXE (1983). This is the “ADHD” edition, which is the 5 minute original runtime compressed into a byte sized 10 second chunk.
